Global Electricity Meters Market Insights
Electricity Meters Market size was valued at USD 21.3 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 32.5 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 6.7% from 2024 to 2030.

Electricity Meters Market Overview
The global electricity meters market is valued at approximately USD 22.5 billion in 2024 and is projected to reach USD 30.1 billion by 2030, growing at a compound annual growth rate (CAGR) of 5.1%. The adoption of smart grids and the increasing demand for accurate and real-time monitoring of electricity consumption are primary growth drivers. Electricity meters, including traditional and smart meters, are essential in managing energy consumption, billing, and monitoring. This market is witnessing significant transformation due to technological advancements, regulatory frameworks, and the growing need for energy-efficient solutions in residential, commercial, and industrial sectors.

